ğŸ“– What is Load Average?
The load average is a measure of system activity, 
showing the average number of processes that are either running or waiting for CPU or I/O over a period of time.

load average: 1.23, 0.85, 0.65
These correspond to:
1.23 â†’ average over the last 1 minute
0.85 â†’ average over the last 5 minutes
0.65 â†’ average over the last 15 minutes

ğŸ“– How to Check Load Average:
uptime
top
cat /proc/loadavg

ğŸ“Œ Load Average Includes:
âœ… Processes running on CPU
âœ… Processes waiting for CPU
âœ… Processes in uninterruptible sleep (like waiting for disk I/O)
It does not count sleeping or idle processes.

ğŸ“Œ Rule of Thumb:
Load Average vs CPU Cores	System Health
Load <= Number of CPU Cores	Healthy
Load > Number of CPU Cores	Overloaded
